{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Marcus Bettinelli | image = Marcus Bettinelli 12-04-2014 1.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = Bettinelli playing for [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] in 2014 | fullname = Marcus Bettinelli<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/844127 |title=2018/19 Premier League squads confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=3 September 2018 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|5|24|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.co.uk/player/177545/marcus-bettinelli |title=Marcus Bettinelli |website=ESPN FC |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Camberwell]], England | height = {{convert|1.94|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/player-profiles/marcus-bettinelli |title=Marcus Bettinelli |publisher=Fulham F.C. |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | currentclub = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | clubnumber = 1 | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2010 | youthclubs1 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | years1 = 2010– | clubs1 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | caps1 = 89 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2012–2013 | clubs2 = → [[Dartford F.C.|Dartford]] (loan) | caps2 = 35 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2013 | clubs3 = → [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] (loan) | caps3 = 17 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2014 | clubs4 = → [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] (loan) | caps4 = 22 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2015 | nationalteam1 = [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = 17:58, 15 November 2018 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = }} '''Marcus Bettinelli''' (born 24 May 1992) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|Fulham}} club [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. He has been capped by the [[England national under-21 football team|England national under-21 team]] and called up for the [[England national football team|senior team]].
==Club career== Bettinelli was born in [[Camberwell]], London.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/marcus-bettinelli-239791/ |title=Marcus Bettinelli |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> He started his career with [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]], signing his first professional contract in July 2010.<ref>{{Hugman|26032|accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref>
Bettinelli joined [[National League (division)|Conference Premier]] club [[Dartford F.C.|Dartford]] on 17 August 2012 on a one-month [[Loan (sports)|loan]] to gain first-team experience.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2012/august/17/bettinelli-loan-deal |title=Bettinelli loan deal |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=17 August 2012 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> He made his debut a day later, in a 2–0 away loss against [[Macclesfield Town F.C.|Macclesfield Town]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2012/august/21/bettinelli-makes-darts-debut |title=Bettinelli makes Darts debut |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=21 August 2012 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> Having made seven appearances so far, his loan spell was extended for another month.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2012/september/21/bettenelli-extends-darts-spell |title=Bettinelli extends Darts spell |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=21 September 2012 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> This would happen again, as it was extended until Christmas.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kentonline.co.uk/dartford/news/fulham-goalkeeper-marcus-bettine-a59303/ |title=Fulham goalkeeper Marcus Bettinelli extends loan spell with Blue Square Bet Premier Dartford until Christmas |first=Steve |last=Tervet |website=KentOnline |publisher=KM Group |date=26 October 2012 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> He went on to make 42 appearances in all competitions before being recalled by Fulham on 26 March 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kentonline.co.uk/dartford/news/marcus-bettinelli-returns-to-ful-a54532/ |title=Marcus Bettinelli returns to Fulham from loan spell at Dartford |first=Alex |last=Hoad |website=KentOnline |publisher=KM Group |date=26 March 2013 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref>
Bettinelli joined [[EFL League Two|League Two]] club [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] on 28 August 2013 on a one-month loan.<ref name=loan>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23878140 |title=Fulham: Marcus Bettinelli joins Accrington Stanley on loan |publisher=BBC Sport |date=29 August 2013 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> He made his debut the same day in the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] against [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] in a 2–0 home defeat.<ref name=sb1314/> His [[English Football League|Football League]] debut on 31 August, in a 1–0 home defeat to [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]].￼￼<ref name=sb1314/> Fulham confirmed on 2 September 2013 that Bettinelli would stay with Accrington for the rest of the [[2013–14 Accrington Stanley F.C. season|2013–14 season]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/23931848 |title=Fulham: Marcus Bettinelli to stay at Accrington for full season |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2 September 2013 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> but he was recalled on 26 December<ref>{{cite web |url=http://accringtonstanley.co.uk/2013/12/bettinelli-recalled/ |title=Bettinelli recalled |first=Dan |last=Jewell |publisher=Accrington Stanley F.C. |date=26 December 2013 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> and was named as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in Fulham's 2–1 away win over [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] in the league as cover for [[David Stockdale]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25442183 |title=Norwich City 1–2 Fulham |first=Matt |last=Monaghan |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 December 2013 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> On 3 January 2014, he re-joined Accrington Stanley on loan until 30 January 2014.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25588090 |title=Accrington re-sign Fulham's Marcus Bettinelli on loan |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 January 2014 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref>
Bettinelli agreed a two-year extension to his Fulham contract on 10 January 2014, which would keep him at the club until June 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2014/january/10/new-deal-for-marcus |title=New deal for Marcus |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=10 January 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110125210/http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2014/january/10/new-deal-for-marcus |archivedate=10 January 2014 |deadurl=yes}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 26 August in the second round of the [[EFL Cup|League Cup]] away to West London rivals [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]], keeping a clean sheet in a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/brentford-vs-fulham/report/325020 |title=Capital One Cup: Fulham earn 1-0 win at Brentford |publisher=Sky Sports |date=27 August 2014 |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> Four days later he made his league debut for Fulham in the [[EFL Championship|Championship]], a 1–1 home draw with [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]]. On 5 December, he was sent off after 18 minutes in a 5–0 loss to Watford at [[Craven Cottage]] for fouling [[Matěj Vydra]], conceding a penalty that [[Troy Deeney]] put past substitute goalkeeper [[Gábor Király]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30241297 |title=Fulham 0–5 Watford |publisher=BBC Sport |date=5 December 2014 |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>
Bettinelli signed another contract extension on 30 August 2017, keeping him at Fulham until June 2020 with an option in the club's favour to extend for a further year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2017/august/30/marcus-bettinelli-new-deal |title=Bettinelli's new deal |publisher=Fulham F.C. |date=30 August 2017 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> He was second-choice to [[David Button]] for all but the last six matches of the [[2016–17 EFL Championship]] season and thought that his Fulham career was over, but manager [[Slaviša Jokanović]] eventually made him the starting goalkeeper for the following season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/marcus-bettinelli-admits-thought-fulham-14488693 |title=Marcus Bettinelli admits he thought his Fulham career was over last season |first=Ryan |last=O'Donovan |website=Get West London |publisher=Reach |date=3 April 2018 |accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> Fulham finished third and qualified for the [[2018 EFL play-offs|play-offs]], defeating [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] 2–1 on aggregate in the semi-final and [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] 1–0 in the [[2018 EFL Championship play-off Final|final]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref name=sb1718/><ref name=playoffs/>
==International career== In November 2014, Bettinelli was called up to the [[England national under-21 football team|England U21]] squad for the first time for matches against [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal]] and [[France national under-21 football team|France]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2014/nov/06/squad-named-for-portugal-france-061114 |title=England under-21s squad named for double header |first=Nicholas |last=Veevers |publisher=The Football Association |date=6 November 2014 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> He made his debut for the under-21 side in a friendly against the [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|Czech Republic]] on 27 March 2015 in a 1–0 away win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/27/czech-republic-england-under-21s-friendly-match-report |title=Tom Carroll scores winner for England under-21s against Czech Republic |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |agency=Press Association |date=27 March 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> This proved to be his only appearance for the under-21 team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.englandfootballonline.com/MatchRsl/MatchRslTmU21pg4.html |title=England's matches: The under 21's: 2010–20 |website=England Football Online |publisher=Chris Goodwin, Glen Isherwood & Peter Young |date=7 September 2018 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref>
In September 2018, he was called up to the [[England national football team|England]] squad for matches against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] and [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45413352 |title=England call up Marcus Bettinelli as Adam Lallana withdraws |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=4 September 2018 |date=4 September 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== He is the son of [[Fulham F.C. Academy|Fulham Academy]] goalkeeping coach Vic Bettinelli.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/chelsea/11547224/Chelsea-want-Fulhams-England-U-21-keeper-Marcus-Bettinelli-to-replace-Petr-Cech.html |title=Chelsea want Fulham's England U-21 keeper Marcus Bettinelli to replace Petr Cech |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |location=London |first=Jason |last=Burt |date=18 April 2015 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}</ref> Bettinelli is of partial Italian descent on his father's side.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/fulham-goalkeeper-im-happier-earning-less-if-it-means-that-i-get-to-play-59j0rlvcw |title=Fulham goalkeeper: I'm happier earning less if it means that I get to play |first=Henry |last=Winter |newspaper=The Times |location=London |date=29 April 2017 |accessdate=7 September 2018}}{{subscription required|s}}</ref>
