{{Infobox football biography | name = Ibrahima Cissé | image = | fullname = Ibrahima Cissé<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/efl-documents/efl-professional-retain-list--free-transfers---2017-18.pdf |title=Club list of registered players: As at 19th May 2018: Fulham |publisher=English Football League |format=PDF |page=16 |accessdate=17 June 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1994|2|28|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Liège]], Belgium<ref>http://www.goal.com/en-tza/news/fifa-approve-fulhams-ibrahima-cisse-switch-from-belgium-to/arxvkw74vaxk127mdp7tw1l7h</ref> | height = 1.84 m | position = [[Midfielder (association football)|Defensive midfielder]] / [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]] | currentclub = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | clubnumber = 44 | youthyears1= 2005–2012 |youthclubs1 = [[Standard Liège]] | years1 = 2012–2014 | clubs1 = [[Standard Liège]] | caps1 = 34 | goals1 = 1 | years2 = 2014–2016 | clubs2 = [[KV Mechelen]] | caps2 = 48 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2016–2017 | clubs3 = [[Standard Liège]] | caps3 = 17 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2017– | clubs4 = [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] | caps4 = 9 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2010–2011 | nationalteam1 = [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 14 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2011 | nationalteam2 = Belgium U18 | nationalcaps2 = 2 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2012 | nationalteam3 = [[Belgium national under-19 football team|Belgium U19]] | nationalcaps3 = 3 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalyears4 = 2012–2015 | nationalteam4 = [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium U21]] | nationalcaps4 = 10 | nationalgoals4 = 0 | nationalyears5 = 2018– | nationalteam5 = [[Guinea national football team|Guinea]] | nationalcaps5 = 2 | nationalgoals5 = 1 | pcupdate = 09:12, 10 February 2019 (UTC) | ntupdate = 12 October 2018 }} '''Ibrahima Cissé''' (born 28 February 1994) is a footballer who plays for [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]]. Born in Belgium, Cissé represents the [[Guinea national football team]] internationally.
==Career== ===Fulham=== Fulham tried to sign Cissé from Belgium side [[Standard Liège]] in January 2017 but it wasn't until 7 July 2017 that Fulham finally signed him for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11681/10720468/fulham-hold-talks-with-standard-liege-to-sign-ibrahima-cisse |title=Fulham hold talks with Standard Liege to sign Ibrahima Cisse |publisher=Sky Sports |author=Lyall Thomas |date=7 January 2017 |accessdate=8 July 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fulhamfc.com/news/2017/july/07/cisse-signs |title=Cisse Signs |publisher=Fulham Football Club |date= 7 July 2017 |accessdate=8 July 2017 }}</ref>
==International career== Cissé was born in Belgium and is of Guinean descent. He was formerly a youth international for Belgium. However, he pledged his international allegiance to Guinea in March 2018.<ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43590375</ref>
On 25 April 2018, Cissé accepted an invitation to represent the [[Guinea national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.afrik-foot.com/guinee-apres-seka-3-nouveaux-binationaux-disent-oui|title=Guinée : après Seka, 3 nouveaux binationaux disent oui - Afrik-foot.com : l'actualité du football africain|website=www.afrik-foot.com}}</ref> He made his professional debut for Guinea in a 1-0 [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] win over [[Central African Republic national football team|Central African Republic]] on 9 September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cafonline.com/en-us/competitions/32ndeditionoftotalafricacupofnations/MatchDetails?MatchId=owNhdRjYIdDzTEAyxtDiW2kQIwXjM8B3NHZ1Lek2qNhXOgH6h16nzfF4DCuKHVOd|title=Guinea - Central African Republic 09/09/2018|website=www.cafonline.com}}</ref>
